---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="DayZ Standalone Scripting for Beginners - DZ Academy">
  <header class="hero">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>DayZ Standalone Scripting for Beginners (v1.20+)</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">by Big Grampa - DZ Academy</p>
      <p class="description">
        Learn to create mods for DayZ Standalone from scratch, even with no prior programming experience
      </p>
      <a href="/chapter1" class="cta-button">Start Learning</a>
    </div>
  </header>

  <main class="container">
    <section class="intro">
      <h2>Welcome to DayZ Standalone Modding & Scripting</h2>
      <p>
        This web-based book will teach you how to create mods for DayZ Standalone (version 1.20 and above) 
        from scratch, even if you have no prior programming or modding experience. We'll start with the 
        absolute basics and gradually build up your knowledge, chapter by chapter.
      </p>
      <p>
        By the end, you'll have built a simple mod – a clothes storage locker with a code lock where you 
        can stash items – and learned a ton of DayZ scripting concepts along the way.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="chapters">
      <h2>Chapter Overview</h2>
      <div class="chapter-grid">
        <div class="chapter-card">
          <h3>Chapter 1</h3>
          <h4>Introduction to DayZ Modding</h4>
          <p>Learn what DayZ Standalone modding is and why this guide was created for beginners.</p>
          <a href="/chapter1" class="chapter-link">Read Chapter 1</a>
        </div>
        
        <div class="chapter-card">
          <h3>Chapter 2</h3>
          <h4>Setting Up Your Modding Environment</h4>
          <p>Install and configure the necessary tools to start creating DayZ mods.</p>
          <a href="/chapter2" class="chapter-link">Read Chapter 2</a>
        </div>
        
        <div class="chapter-card">
          <h3>Chapter 3</h3>
          <h4>Enforce Script Basics</h4>
          <p>Learn the fundamentals of Enforce Script, the language used for DayZ modding.</p>
          <a href="/chapter3" class="chapter-link">Read Chapter 3</a>
        </div>
        
        <div class="chapter-card">
          <h3>Chapter 4</h3>
          <h4>Understanding Classes and Objects</h4>
          <p>Explore object-oriented programming concepts essential for DayZ modding.</p>
          <a href="/chapter4" class="chapter-link">Read Chapter 4</a>
        </div>
        
        <div class="chapter-card">
          <h3>Chapter 5</h3>
          <h4>Creating the Clothes Locker Item</h4>
          <p>Configure and add a new item to the game with proper properties.</p>
          <a href="/chapter5" class="chapter-link">Read Chapter 5</a>
        </div>
        
        <div class="chapter-card">
          <h3>Chapter 6</h3>
          <h4>Scripting the Lock Mechanism</h4>
          <p>Implement the locking functionality for our custom storage container.</p>
          <a href="/chapter6" class="chapter-link">Read Chapter 6</a>
        </div>
        
        <div class="chapter-card">
          <h3>Chapter 7</h3>
          <h4>Testing and Playing</h4>
          <p>Learn how to test your mod and experiment with different configurations.</p>
          <a href="/chapter7" class="chapter-link">Read Chapter 7</a>
        </div>
        
        <div class="chapter-card">
          <h3>Chapter 8</h3>
          <h4>Conclusion and Next Steps</h4>
          <p>Recap what you've learned and discover paths for further modding adventures.</p>
          <a href="/chapter8" class="chapter-link">Read Chapter 8</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="about">
      <h2>About This Guide</h2>
      <p>
        This guide is written for total beginners. You don't need any programming background or modding experience. 
        We'll start from zero, explaining concepts in a fun, intuitive way. Each chapter builds on the last, 
        so by following in order, you'll gradually gain both programming skills and DayZ-specific modding knowledge.
      </p>
      <p>
        Along the way, we'll include examples, code snippets, and even some small challenges to test your understanding. 
        By the end, you'll have created a working DayZ mod: a Clothes Locker that acts as a storage container with a 
        (simulated) code lock.
      </p>
    </section>
  </main>

  <footer>
    <div class="container">
      <p>&copy; 2023 DZ Academy - DayZ Modding Tutorial</p>
    </div>
  </footer>
</Layout>

<style>
  .hero {
    background-color: var(--primary);
    color: var(--text);
    padding: 4rem 0;
    text-align: center;
  }
  
  .hero h1 {
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    margin: 0;
  }
  
  .subtitle {
    font-style: italic;
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
  }
  
  .description {
    max-width: 600px;
    margin: 1.5rem auto;
    font-size: 1.2rem;
  }
  
  .cta-button {
    display: inline-block;
    background-color: var(--highlight);
    color: white;
    padding: 0.8rem 2rem;
    border-radius: 4px;
    text-decoration: none;
    font-weight: bold;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    transition: background-color 0.3s;
  }
  
  .cta-button:hover {
    background-color: #e06a40;
  }
  
  .intro, .chapters, .about {
    margin: 3rem 0;
  }
  
  .chapter-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(300px, 1fr));
    gap: 2rem;
    margin-top: 2rem;
  }
  
  .chapter-card {
    border: 1px solid #ddd;
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    transition: transform 0.3s, box-shadow 0.3s;
  }
  
  .chapter-card:hover {
    transform: translateY(-5px);
    box-shadow: 0 10px 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
  }
  
  .chapter-card h3 {
    color: var(--highlight);
    margin: 0;
  }
  
  .chapter-card h4 {
    margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem;
  }
  
  .chapter-link {
    display: inline-block;
    margin-top: 1rem;
    padding: 0.5rem 1rem;
    background-color: var(--secondary);
    color: white;
    text-decoration: none;
    border-radius: 4px;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    transition: background-color 0.3s;
  }
  
  .chapter-link:hover {
    background-color: var(--primary);
  }
  
  footer {
    background-color: var(--primary);
    color: var(--text);
    padding: 1rem 0;
    text-align: center;
    margin-top: 3rem;
  }
  
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .hero {
      padding: 3rem 0;
    }
    
    .hero h1 {
      font-size: 2rem;
    }
    
    .description {
      font-size: 1rem;
    }
  }
</style>
